J. B. KERLEY and Frank Silva, Appellants, v. UNITED STATES of America, Appellee. No. 11351. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. June 12, 1946. Walter H. Duane, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. Frank J. Hennessy, U. S. Atty., and Reynold H. Colvin, Asst. U. S. Atty., both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before GARRECHT, HEALY and BONE, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon consideration of the stipulation of counsel for respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, it is ordered that the appeal in this cause be, and hereby is dismissed, that a judgment be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court in this cause issue forthwith.
